75622914-d144-4f59-b21a-92c58c59736a.do_description: To make the output, you have to...make a 90 degree line through each color. The line from blue will go up and down. The line from red will go left and right
75622914-d144-4f59-b21a-92c58c59736a.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input
75622914-d144-4f59-b21a-92c58c59736a.see_description: In the input, you should see...a black grid with a blue unit and a red unit.

787613a3-49e1-4b0e-8ec8-2054f62ac060.do_description: To make the output, you have to...make a L shape in orange to connect the red and blue blocks.
787613a3-49e1-4b0e-8ec8-2054f62ac060.grid_description: The output grid size...should remain the same size as the input grid.
787613a3-49e1-4b0e-8ec8-2054f62ac060.see_description: In the input, you should see...one light blue block and one red block.

ed6a6df0-b487-4409-a458-c29bb6bd2a09.do_description: To make the output, you have to...draw a down line with yellow to which the red grid's row meet. and continue the yellow grid to the side of the red grid
ed6a6df0-b487-4409-a458-c29bb6bd2a09.grid_description: The output grid size...same as the input grid. copy the input grid.
ed6a6df0-b487-4409-a458-c29bb6bd2a09.see_description: In the input, you should see... the blue grid only.
